      </prefercite>
      <bioghist id="aspace_3aef406accb0fc2b52c11d875cfbfdf7">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Mercedes Moore DeMare was born on November 7, 1910 in Brooklyn, New York. She graduated from Smith College in 1931 and received a M.F.A. from the Yale University School of the Fine Arts in 1936. Her costume and scenic designs appeared in various Broadway productions during the 1930s and 1940s.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <arrangement id="aspace_85682233e6552c3059d15fc6b1c14008">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Arranged by type of material.</p>  
      </arrangement>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_a920620f9c988ccedfbfbbd04710da32">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The papers consist of student notebooks, syllabi, and other course materials belonging to Mercedes Moore DeMare, a 1936 M.F.A. graduate of the drama program in the Yale University School of the Fine Arts.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
